A data policy is a short statement of management intent and fundamental rules governing the creation, acquisition, integrity, security, quality, and use of data and information [source: DAMA DM_BOK, http://www.dama.org.]. A data policy can be among others the following:
- information security policy;
- privacy policy;
- licensing and charging policy ;
- data quality policy; and
- metadata management policy.
